Class TextGlyph

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractTreeNode

    public class TextGlyph
extends AbstractReferenceGlyph
    The TextGlyph class describes the position and dimension of text labels. It inherits from GraphicalObject and adds the attributes graphicalObject, text and originOfText.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Nicolas Rodriguez, Sebastian Frölich, Andreas Dräger, David Vetter

      • setGraphicalObject

        public void setGraphicalObject(java.lang.String graphicalObject)
        The graphicalObject attribute contains the id of any GraphicalObject and specifies that the TextGlyph should be considered to be a label to that object. This allows modelers to indicate that the label is to be moved together with the object. If the graphicalObject attribute is used together with the metaidRef they need to refer to the same object in the Layout.
        Parameters:
        graphicalObject -

      • setOriginOfText

        public void setOriginOfText(NamedSBase originOfText)
        Parameters:
        originOfText -

      • setOriginOfText

        public void setOriginOfText(java.lang.String originOfText)
        Additionally the optional attribute originOfText holds the id of an entity in the Model. If it is specified, the text to be displayed is taken from the name attribute of the referenced object. If both attributes originOfText and text are specified, the text attribute value overrides the value of originOfText.
        Parameters:
        originOfText -
